    %section
      %h1 What is a share (stock)?
      %p
        A share(stock) is defined as a part ownership of a company. Initially, shares  are sold by the owners of the company to the public in an Initial Public Offering,  generally  to finance the company’s expansion. After the Initial Public Offering (IPO), the shares are traded on an exchange such as the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) or National Stock Exchange (NSE), where an investor can purchase and sell shares. Small investors cannot transact directly with exchange. They need to open an account with a brokerage firm(e.g. Kotak Securities, ICICI Securities) which acts as an intermediary between the investor and the exchange.
    %section
      %h1 Shares and Investment return
      %p
        Investors enjoy returns in 2 forms:
      %ul
        %li
          %b
            Capital Gain:
          Shares often appreciate in price over time. The difference between the purchase price and selling price of the shares is called capital gain. This is the main form of return from shares.
        %li
          %b
            Dividends:
          Companies often pay out a part of their profits to the shareholder. The share of profits which a company distributes to its shareholders is called dividend. Dividends are usually quite small are rarely yield over 2% p.a.
      %p
        The share price of a company is largely dictated by the company’s performance. If the company is performing well, the share price goes up.
        Similarly if the company performs poorly the share price goes down. Apart from company’s performance, the share price is also influenced by the trend and sentiment of the market.
        A positive sentiment and upward trend usually help to push the price up while a negative sentiment and downward trend may push the shares price down. Read our article on
        #{link_to 'fundamental analysis',main_app.page_path('investment_education/fundamental-analysis-shares')}
        to gain an insight on how to evaluate a company’s performance and
        #{link_to 'what moves share markets',main_app.page_path('investment_education/share-market')}
        to understand how market sentiments effects the share market.
